Teachers have planned a strike in January when schools open.Nurses, clinical officers, police officers, youth and women all have different grievances against this government. This week, doctors were supposed to be on strike, but they postponed it to allow for talks with the government. The same government that sold donated protective gear.
The same government that has not paid their salaries and insurance cover against the very disease they are supposed to be helping Kenyans fight.



