But they are not alone. Teachers have planned a strike in January when schools open. Nurses, clinical officers, police officers, youth and women all have different grievances against this government.
Given how the past seven years have panned out for Kenyans, it should be clear by now that demonstrations, strikes, begging and petitioning this government does not work.
 How do you convince the same person who sold donated personal protective equipment to issue them?  How can someone stab you and you run back to them for healing?



