The only way any of these groups is going to get good working conditions is if the system of governance works. 
Kenyans put in place this bad government, which has overseen wanton corruption, breakdown of the rule of law, retrogression, a dying economy and rising debt, and only they can remove it. But that won't happen if we keep on dividing themselves into small groups of victims.
They say tough times call for tough measures. It is time doctors looked to their patients for help, for teachers to beseech their students’ parents for support. 
Calling on Kenyans for support means ensuring that the next batch of leaders get into office knowing that all Kenyans — not just doctors — are extremely invested in ensuring that the Ministry of Health works.



